g mobs with those epics for more damage due to higher skill caps because of lvling. I feel that our epic needs to scale with us post 60 just as all the other melee epics scale with them. I never see a ranger backpack his swithwind because he is fighting a lvl 63 mob and can't land a hit on lvl 63 mobs. /shrug <br>
<br>
I seriously consider this to be broken. There is no reason for a mage to do the epic anymore. The new pets can hit all mobs and the mage quest is still a bitch to do. Makes more since the put the work into leveling and hitting 61 and getting better then epic pets. Rich Waters said the other day to monks that those monks that put in the work to get those better weapons should not be out done by other monks that just happen to lvl to 65 and get 18/20 fist automatically. He said that if you want better you should have to work for it and 5 lvls is such a small thing that it doesn't justify the average monk having better damage then most uber monks. As it stands the average mage in a Bone Caster Robe with the lvl 61/62 pets has a better pet then the mage that is in ssra temple with no new pet scrolls even if said mage has epic. This should be fixed asap. I am going to find that quote and post it.<br>
<br>
