<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Even given the sacrifice of stats from held weapons, making all monk fists 18/20 weapons at level 65 is very unbalanced. Look at the state of weapons today - go browse through the profiles of the most uber monks - an 18/20 weapon is very close to the best available in the game, and the pure damage dealing potential is only a small percentage off from the best there is. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>There is no compelling reason to make it so the very average monk and the most uber monk are doing about the same damage at level 65.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> The difference in stats for keeping your hands free doesn't <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>justify such an enormous jump in damage just for hitting level 65. If a monk invests the time and effort to attaining the best available gear in the game, he deserves to have significant damage advantage over the monk who does not.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
To me this screams to what i have been saying the past two weeks. A mage that didn't put in the work should not just &quot;ding 61&quot; and get a pet that is better then the mage epic. Mages that put in the work should be better then those who have not. Rich states clearly that leveling isn't equal to putting in &quot;time and effort&quot;. A mage that put in the time and effort should have a better pet then the mage that did not. I will be emailing Absor and sending a email to have the mage epic not made worthless just because of five new levels. Also I am going to use this quote from Rich in that email. IMO if it works this way for monks it should work the same for mages.<br>
